<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FFB4EF77FF42FA12FDF8F995" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB4EF77FF42FA12FB38F9B1" blockId="28.[151,1436,1374,1582]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB4EF77FF42FA12FEE7FA79" bold="true" box="[199,338,1447,1473]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Comments:</emphasis>
This is the first record of the species after its original description. Even if few males of the species were collected so far, the species seems to reflect a broad geographic distribution, since it was previously recorded in Central West and Northeast regions of 
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFFB4EF77FDE3FA5AFD1BF9B1" box="[614,686,1519,1545]" name="Brazil" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Females of this species are still unknown.
</paragraph>
